      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "keywords": [],
        "power": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Whenever an adjacent enemy grabs the daybringer or uses a melee ability against them, that enemy takes [[/damage 3 poison]] damage.</p>",
          "director": ""
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Wet",
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "keywords": [],
        "power": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Angulotls make use of a unique effect called “wet.” While wet, an angulotl doesn’t provoke opportunity attacks by moving. At the same time, any non-angulotl who is wet and ends their turn with none of their movement remaining slips and falls prone. Several angulotl abilities can impose this effect, but a creature in an encounter featuring angulotls can also become wet by entering water, as the Director determines.</p>",
          "director": ""
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Moisturizing End Effect",
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "keywords": [],
        "power": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>At the end of each of the daybringer’s turns, they can either take [[/damage 5]] damage or end the wet effect on an adjacent creature in order to end one effect on them that can be ended by a saving throw. This damage can’t be reduced in any way.</p>",
          "director": ""
        }
      }
